The garden is 220 * 120 = <<220*120=24600>>24600 square feet.
The tilled land will take up half the area, and the trellises and raised beds will be the other half. Each half is 24600 / 2 = <<24600/2=12300>>12300 square feet.
The trellises will take up 1/3 of the remaining land, so the raised beds will take 1 - 1/3 = 2/3 of the remaining land.
So the total area of the raised bed area will be 12300 square feet * (2/3) = <<12300*(2/3)=8200>>8200 square feet.
#### 8200
